    <h1>The Man Who Planted Forests</h1>
    <p>
      Elzéard Bouffier, a fictional character from Jean Giono’s short story, is a humble shepherd who single-handedly reforests a barren valley in France by planting acorns daily. Though fictional, his story is often referenced for its powerful environmental message and its portrayal of quiet, consistent efforts creating massive change.
    </p>
